6.body: Refrain from using accessories that may promote any groups that are unrelated to their roles and are not said to be allowed in this document Refer to the conservative and formal side, when in doubt
6.title: All attendees must:

7.body: Should always wear three-piece(jacket, pants, dress shirt) suits. Accessories: Mandatory: Neck/Bow tie Allowed: Rings Belts Lapel/Tie pins (as long as it doesn't violate the first rule) Suspenders Cufflinks/Earrings/clips (as long as it doesn't violate the first rule) Pocket Squares Watches Refrain from: Bracelets Hats Gloves Necklaces Graphic ties Chains Shirts: Refrain from: Graphic shirts Flamboyant colors Allowed collars: Classic Semi-Spread Spread Button Down Wings Small Wings Unallowed Collars Eyelet Mandarin Bands Standing Jacket & Pants: Always wear matching suits Italian style is recommended Prefer darker colors Refrain from informal patterns Always use formal shoes
7.title: Male attendees:

8.body: Should wear Pants/skirts/dresses The minimum skirt length is two fingers lower than knee length Should refrain from informal patterns flamboyant colors Shirts: Refrain from: Graphic Shirts Flamboyant colors Revealing styles Maximum reveal can be three fingers under the neckline Always use formal shoes Are encouraged to wear Jackets There are no required accessories for female delegates however it is allowed to wear these: Jewelry (as long as it doesn't violate the first rule) Foulard (refrain from flamboyant colors and informal patterns) Hair accessories (crowns are only permitted for the delegates and chair board in the crisis committees) Watches Pins(as long as it doesn't violate the first rule)
